# Onsite Coding Standards

**TypeScript/React:** Functional components, hooks, full typing (no any). Log and rethrow errors with cause. Async/await; handle loading and error in UI.

**Python:** Type hints, Pydantic for API. No secrets in code; use env. Specific exceptions; log before raise when useful.

**CSV/Data:** UTF-8 (BOM if Excel). Validate headers and required columns. Use consistent date/revenue parsers (see onsite-data-analytics).

**Tests:** Unit test parsing and business rules. Name: test_<what>_<expected>. Fixtures small and realistic; no production data.

**Security:** No hardcoded keys. Validate/sanitize uploads; limit size/rows.
